  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <div class="page-wrap">

    <h1 class="page-title">History</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">"Those who do not learn from history are condemned to repeat it."</p>
    <div class="notice-box">This website has been created for cultural and historical purposes only. It is in no way the tool of any political ideology.</div>

    <div class="timeline">

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>9 Sept.<br/>1944</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/1-Partizan.jfif" alt="Coup d'état 1944" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>The Coup d'état</h3>
              <p>Communist partisans backed by the USSR overthrow the royalist government allied with Nazi Germany. The beginning of socialism in Bulgaria.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>15 Sept.<br/>1946</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/2-Referendum.jpg" alt="Referendum 1946" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>Referendum — People's Republic</h3>
              <p>The 1946 referendum takes place on September 15th. The country is declared a People's Republic.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>6 Dec.<br/>1947</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/3-GeorgiDimitrov.jpg" alt="Georgi Dimitrov Constitution" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>Georgi Dimitrov Constitution</h3>
              <p>The Georgi Dimitrov Constitution is adopted and remains in force until 1971.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>2 Jul.<br/>1949</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/4-Mosoleum.jpg" alt="Georgi Dimitrov death" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>Death of Georgi Dimitrov</h3>
              <p>Georgi Dimitrov dies on July 2nd, 1949, and is displayed in the Georgi Dimitrov Mausoleum.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>20 Dec.<br/>1949</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/5-Valko.webp" alt="Valko Chervenkov" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>Valko Chervenkov takes power</h3>
              <p>Valko Chervenkov succeeds Georgi Dimitrov as General Secretary of the Communist Party until 1954.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>4 Mar.<br/>1954</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/6-Todor.jpg" alt="Todor Zhivkov" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>Todor Zhivkov rises to power</h3>
              <p>Todor Zhivkov succeeds Valko Chervenkov as head of the Communist Party. He becomes the longest-serving leader (non-monarchy) in Bulgarian history.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>28 Mar.<br/>1965</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/7-TodorBis.jpg" alt="April Conspiracy" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>The April Conspiracy</h3>
              <p>The "April Conspiracy" is revealed on March 28th, 1965. The attempted coup d'état aimed to overthrow Todor Zhivkov.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>8 May<br/>1971</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/8-TodorConstitution.jpg" alt="Zhivkov Constitution" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>Zhivkov Constitution</h3>
              <p>The "Zhivkov Constitution" is established and remains in force until the end of the People's Republic of Bulgaria.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>10 Apr.<br/>1979</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/9-Georgi-Ivanov.jpg" alt="Georgi Ivanov cosmonaut" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>First Bulgarian Cosmonaut</h3>
              <p>Bulgaria's first cosmonaut Georgi Ivanov is launched into space on the Soyuz 33 mission.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>6 May<br/>1981</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/10-MilleAns.jpg" alt="1300 years Bulgaria" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>1300 Years of Bulgaria</h3>
              <p>The Bulgarian nation celebrates 1300 years of existence. The largest military parade in Sofia's history takes place on this occasion.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>23 Aug.<br/>1981</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/11-Buzludzha.jpg" alt="Buzludzha monument" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>Buzludzha Monument Inaugurated</h3>
              <p>The monumental house of the Bulgarian Communist Party "Buzludzha" is inaugurated.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>10 Nov.<br/>1989</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="history/12-Protests.webp" alt="Fall of communism" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>End of Zhivkov's Rule</h3>
              <p>One day after the fall of the Berlin Wall, communist leader Todor Zhivkov is removed from his position as General Secretary of the Communist Party.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="tl-date"><span>15 Nov.<br/>1990</span></div>
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <div class="tl-content-inner">
            <div class="tl-img"><img src="/history/13dCommunism.jpg" alt="End of People's Republic" /></div>
            <div class="tl-text">
              <h3>End of the People's Republic</h3>
              <p>The Assembly votes to rename the country the Republic of Bulgaria and removes the communist emblem from the national flag.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div><!-- end timeline -->
  </div><!-- end page-wrap -->

